<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 17 at 3:04PM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...A WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IS IN EFFECT THROUGH 3 AM...
WEATHER...
* Light snow will increase in coverage this afternoon. Snowfall
will peak in intensity this evening, leading to snow covered
and slippery roads for the evening commute. Accumulation of 1
to 2 inches will be possible by 7 pm.
IMPACTS...
* Accumulating snow may lead to slippery roads particularly on
bridges, exit ramps and overpasses.
* Falling snow will result in visibility of mile or less at
times this evening.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* The combination of snow and cold temperatures will result in slippery
conditions and variable traffic rates throughout the county.
Motorists are urged to use caution and account for the variable
driving conditions by allowing extra time.
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
